headline: ZTS Q1 Earnings Call: Guidance Raised as Platform Products Drive Momentum Amid Competitive Pressures
summary: Animal health company Zoetis (NYSE:ZTS) reported Q1 CY2025 results topping the market’s revenue expectations, with sales up 1.4% year on year to $2.22 billion. The company’s full-year revenue guidance of $9.5 billion at the midpoint came in 1.8% above analysts’ estimates. Its non-GAAP profit of $1.48 per share was 5.8% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
